===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|たけ|yomi=k}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=たけ|-}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|sort=たけ|*takai}}.

Theories on derivation include:<ref name="Nipponica">{{R:Nipponica|たけ}}</ref><ref name="KDJ2O"/>
* From {{ja-r|長%生|たけ%お.う}} or {{ja-r|高%生|たか%はえ}}, in reference to the speed at which bamboo grows.
* Cognate with {{ja-r|高|たか}}, {{ja-r|長|たけ}}, {{ja-r|丈|たけ}}, all “height”.
* From {{ja-r|高%景|たか%かけ}} or {{ja-r|つらこえ}}. {{attn|ja|「○の反」}}
* From ''ta'' meaning “tall” ({{ja-r|高い|たかい}}) + ''ke'', ancient combining form of {{ja-r|木|き|tree}}.
* A contraction of {{ja-r|痛%快%茎%延へ|いた%く%き%はへ|rom=itakukihae}}, referring to the speed at which bamboo grows.
* From ''ta'', from {{cog|ko|대|t=bamboo}} (see also {{m|ko|대나무|t=bamboo|lit=bamboo tree}}), + ''ke'', ancient combining form of {{ja-r|木|き}}.
<!--aggregated research by some fellow who runs a blog: [http://ppnetwork.seesaa.net/article/461199145.html]-->

